  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Uncertainty quantification was performed using Monte Carlo propagation of inlet boundary condition variability and blood viscosity uncertainty across the five flow-speed operating points; a screening sensitivity study (Sobol first-order indices) was conducted informally during model development to identify candidate dominant inputs, and its findings informed the UQ parameter selection. The UQ results confirm that hemolysis index predictions remain below the RH < 1 threshold across the sampled input space at the 95th percentile.",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
